In some situations, and anesthesiologist or certified registered nurse anesthetist (CRNA) will intubate a patient as part of administration of general anesthesia for surgery. This is typically done in a planned, controlled environment.&nbsp;
In these circumstances, the standard of care requires a pre-anesthesia assessment, which includes planning for proper management of patients with difficult airways.

